               <desc type="building-data">
                  <p xml:lang="en" source="#bibl000294a-1">The Tianning Monsatery Pagoda is an octagonal stone and brick pagoda 
                     with thirteen eaves constructed in the miyan (密檐, meaning “closely-piled eaves” (Lin 2016, 111) style 
                     in the <term ref = "/keyword/k000047">Liao dynasty</term>. A Liao stele found at the top of the pagoda
                     documents its construction in 1119 supervised by prince Chun, 
                     a military general of the Liao military, under the decree of Emperor Tianzuo, and the 
                     construction was completed in 1120 (Wang and Wang 80). The finial (baoding) of the pagoda 
                     was a <term ref = "/keyword/k000070">Qing dynasty</term> reconstruction. 
                  </p>
                  
               </desc>   
